<TITLE> Leaks lead to closure of Titas Gas well in Brahmanbaria </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Jan 9 (bdnews24.com)  Authorities have decided to stop gas production at a Titas Gas well in order to stop gas emissions over a wide area in Brahmanbaria, said a senior gas official Wednesday. Akher Awal, general manager of Bangladesh Gas Fields Company Limited, told reporters that the decision was taken as the well was defective. Titas Gas Well No 3set up 40 years agohas been emitting gas for years, say authorities. Due to the high pressure of the gas, water is spilling out through tubewells in the area. Closure of the well will curtail 30 million cubit feet in gas production, Awal said. Daily gas production in the gas field would be reduced to 405 million cubic feet, he added. Titas Gas Field has a stock of 5.12 trillion cubic feet of gas. A UAE firm has started work on closure of the well, and is scheduled to complete its work by the end of the month, Awal said. He also told reporters production was expected to start at a new well in Habiganj Gas Field soon with a projected production of 12 million cubic feet. bdnews2
